cff-version: 1.2.0
title: The OIA Reference Model (Open Intelligence Architecture)
message: >-
  If you reference or build upon the OIA Reference Model, please cite it using
  the metadata below.
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: Mark
    family-names: Templeton
    affiliation: Agentics Foundation
abstract: >-
  The Open Intelligence Architecture (OIA) is a vendor-neutral reference model
  for the security, sovereignty, and governance of enterprise intelligent
  systems. It describes ten layers (numbered 0-9), seven cross-layer spans,
  three defining properties of intelligent systems, and four named threat
  surfaces of the agentic era, together with a Lens System of audience-specific
  overlays. The model is additive to existing frameworks (OSI, NIST CSF,
  NIST AI RMF, MITRE ATLAS, OWASP LLM, ISO/IEC 42001) rather than competitive
  with them.
keywords:
  - reference architecture
  - enterprise AI
  - AI security
  - agentic systems
  - AI governance
  - confidential computing
  - AI sovereignty
